tokens.name: Cholesterol
tokens.description: Total Cholesterol measures all cholesterol in your blood. High levels increase heart disease risk.

tokens.name: Triglyceride
tokens.description: Triglycerides are a type of fat in the blood. Elevated levels are a risk factor for heart disease.

tokens.name: HDL Cholesterol
tokens.description: HDL (High-Density Lipoprotein) is the 'good' cholesterol. Higher levels are better for heart health.

tokens.name: Direct LDL
tokens.description: LDL (Low-Density Lipoprotein) is the 'bad' cholesterol. High levels increase heart disease risk.

tokens.name: VLDL
tokens.description: VLDL (Very Low-Density Lipoprotein) carries triglycerides. High levels can contribute to heart disease.

tokens.name: CHOL/HDL Ratio
tokens.description: LDL/HDL Ratio compares bad to good cholesterol. Higher values indicate more risk.

tokens.name: LDL/HDL Ratio
tokens.description: CHOL/HDL Ratio is used to estimate heart disease risk. A lower ratio is generally better.
